ent androids possible\n* [[Dr. Tolian Soran]] (''[[Star Trek Generations]]'') \u2013 El-Aurian scientist desperate to return to the Nexus\n* [[Spock|Mr. Spock]] (''Star Trek: The Original Series'') \u2013 science officer and second-in-command of the ''Enterprise''\n* Dr. [[Mohinder Suresh]] (''[[Heroes (U.S. TV series)|Heroes]]'') \u2013 professor of genetics and parapsychology from India\n* [[B'Elanna Torres]] (''Star Trek: Voyager'') \u2013 chief engineer of ''Voyager''\n* [[T'Pol]] (''Star Trek: Enterprise'') \u2013 second-in-command of the ''Enterprise''-NX01, though the crew relied on her as an acting science officer as well\n* [[Trip Tucker|Charles Tucker III]], a.k.a. \"Trip\" (''Star Trek: Enterprise'') \u2013 chief engineer of the ''Enterprise''-NX01\n* Mrs. Wakeman (''[[My Life as a Teenage Robot]]'') \u2013 XJ-9's creator\n* Dr. [[Rudy Wells]] (novel ''[[Cyborg (novel)|Cyborg]]'' by [[Martin Caidin]]; ''[[The Six Million Dollar Man]]'', ''[[The Bionic Woman]]'') \u2013 cyberneticist\n* [[Howard Wolowitz]] (''[[The Big Bang Theory]]'') \u2013 aerospace engineer at [[California Institute of Technology|Caltech]]\n* Dr. Horace Goodspeed, (''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]'') \u2013 mathematician \n* Dr. Pierre Chang, (''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]'') \u2013 astrophysicist\n\n===[[Mad scientist]]s===\n<!--ONLY fictional characters considered to be mad scientists go here; make sure a character fits the \"mad scientist\" category before adding them into this section - know that real-life mad scientists do not belong on this list.-->\n<!--Characters must be placed in alphabetical order by last name-->\n* Dr. Arthur Arden, a.k.a. Hans Gr\u00fcper (''[[American Horror Story: Asylum]]'')\n* [[Walter Bishop (Fringe)|Walter Bishop]] (''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]'')\n* [[Stranger Things|Martin Brenner]]\n* [[Dollmaker (comics)#Barton Mathis|The Dollmaker]] (''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]'', ''[[Gotham (TV series)|Gotham]]'', ''[[Batman vs. Robin]]'', and [[DC Comics]]) \u2013 serial killer and insane surgeon who makes dolls out of human flesh\n* [[Kamen Rider 555|Masahiko Minami]]\n* [[Dr. Loveless]] (''[[The Wild Wild West]]'')\n* Dr. Benjamin Jeffcoat (''[[My Secret Identity]]'')\n\n==In television animation==\n*[[Professor Venomous]] (''OK KO!: Let's be Heroes'', 2013)\n*[[Pok\u00e9mon Chronicles|Dr. Namba]]\n* [[Danny Phantom|Vlad Plasmius]]\n* [[Marvin the Martian]]\n* [[Miles Dredd]]\n* [[Megatron]]\n* [[Princess Twilight Sparkle]] (''My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic'', 2010)\n* [[Princess Bubblegum]] (''[[Adventure Time]]'') \u2013 beautiful princess who invents and creates the citizens of Candy Kingdom in the land of Ooo\n*Princess [[Entrapta]]\n* Professor Bug (''[[The Backyardigans]]'') \u2013 pseudo-[[steampunk]] mad scientist portrayed by Pablo who bugs all the robots in Mega City\n* [[Professor Frink]] (''[[The Simpsons]]'') \u2013 Springfield's greatest scientific and engineering mind\n* Newton Gimmick (''[[The Adventures of Teddy Ruxpin]]'') \u2013 absent-minded inventor whose inventions do not always work, but who always comes through in the end\n* [[Gadget Hackwrench]] (''[[Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers]]'') \u2013 mouse tinkerer/scientist\n* [[Franz Hopper]] (''[[Code Lyoko]]'') \u2013 genius in quantum physics and computer programming responsible for the creation of the virtual reality Lyoko, malevolent AI XANA and the advanced hardware that support both\n* Van Kleiss (''[[Generator Rex]]'') \u2013 main antagonist\n* [[List of Madagascar (franchise) characters#Kowalski|Kowalski]] (''[[Penguins of Madagascar]])'' \u2013 team's scientist and inventor \n* Doctor Krieger (''[[Archer (2009 TV series)|Archer]]'' TV series) \u2013 head of the ISIS applied research department\n* Dr. Alphonse Mephesto, a.k.a. Dr. Mephesto (''[[South Park]]'') \u2013 mad scientist who specializes in genetic engineering; creates things like animals with multiple buttocks; performs experiments ranging from simple DNA tests to creating a genetic clone of Stan Marsh for his son's science project\n* [[Professor Membrane]] (''[[Invader Zim]]'') \u2013 super-scientist; \"the man without whom this world falls into chaos, and the inventor of Super Toast\"\n* Doctor Mindbender (''[[G.I. Joe: Renegades]]'') \u2013 mad young genius in charge of Cobra's secret Bio-Viper project\n* Jimmy Neutron (''[[The Adventures of Jimmy Neutron: Boy Genius]]'') \u2013 boy genius\n* [[Perceptor]] (''[[Transformers (toyline)|Transformers]]'') \u2013 [[Autobot]] scientist\n* [[Peridot]] (''[[Steven Universe]]'') \u2013 gem scientist and guardian of the crystal gems\n* Stanford \"Ford\" Pines (''[[Gravity Falls]]'') \u2013 author of the three journals and earned his Ph.D. in Backupsmore University\n* Dr. Benton Quest (''[[Jonny Quest]]'')\n* [[Asami Sato]] (''[[Legend of Korra]]'') \u2013 trained engineer, skilled pilot and driver, and competent unarmed combatant; partner of Avatar Korra and CEO of Future Industries\n* Ratchet (''[[Transformers series|Transformers]]'' series) \u2013 skilled [[Autobot]] [[medic]]; in the G1 Comics, he sacrifices himself to kill [[Megatron (Transformers)|Megatron]]\n* [[Professor Utonium]] (''[[Powerpuff Girls]]'') \u2013 father/scientist who created the Powerpuff Girls, among several other wacky things\n* Wheeljack (''Transformers'') \u2013 [[Autobot]] engineer and inventor\n* [[Doctor Zoidberg]] (''[[Futurama]]'') \u2013 lobster-like creature working as the company doctor for Planet Express\n* Aviva Corcovado (Wild Kratts) - engineer and inventor\n\n===Mad scientists===\n* Dr. Arkeville (''[[The Transformers (TV series)|The Transformers]]'' TV series) \u2013 self-proclaimed evil genius who allies himself with the [[Decepticons]]\n* Professor Bug (''[[The Backyardigans]]'') \u2013 pseudo-[[steampunk]] mad scientist portrayed by Pablo who bugs all the robots in Mega City\n* Professor Finbarr Calamitous (''[[The Adventures of Jimmy Neutron: Boy Genius]]'') \n* Dexter (''[[Dexter's Laboratory]]'') \u2013