us dimensions with his grandson Morty\n* Dr. Weird (''[[Aqua Teen Hunger Force]]'') \u2013 smartest, madest, and scientistest scientist in the universe whose experiments often cause problems for the Aqua Teens.\n\n==In animated films==\n* Megamind (''[[Megamind]]'')\n* [[Princess Twilight Sparkle]] (''My Little Pony: The Movie'', 2017)\n* Dr. Cockroach (''[[Monsters vs. Aliens]]'') \u2013 brilliant professor and a mad scientist with the head, body and abilities of a cockroach\n* Gru (''[[Despicable Me]]'')\n* Dr. Jumba Jookiba (''Lilo & Stitch'', 2002)\n* Dr. Nefario (''[[Despicable Me]]'')\n* [[Tinkerbell|Tinker Bell]]\n* Victor \"Vector\" Perkins (''[[Despicable Me]]'')\n* [[Dr. Wily|Dr. Albert W. Wily]] (''[[Mega Man]]'')\n\n== In manga and anime==\n* [[Dr. Tenma]], creator of [[Astro Boy]].\n* [[List of Case Closed characters#Major supporting characters|Dr. Hiroshi Agasa]] (''[[Case Closed|Detective Conan]]''), an absent-minded professor who creates all of Shinichi's gadgets.\n* ''[[Dr. Slump]]''\n** [[List of Dr. Slump characters#Main_characters|Dr. Senbei Norimaki]], a brilliant but lecherous scientist, who created the protagonist robot [[Arale Norimaki|Arale]].\n** [[List of Dr. Slump characters#Supporting characters|Dr. Mashirito]], Senbei's evil mad scientist rival. Creator of [[List of Dr. Slump characters#Main_characters|Obotchaman]].\n* [[List of Dr. Stone characters#Main_characters|Senku Ishigami]] (''[[Dr. Stone]]''), a highly-intelligent high-school scientific genius, set to restore human civilization by reinventing all the lost technology.\n[[List of Dr. Stone characters|Chrome]] (''[[Dr. Stone]]''), a scientist who helps Senku with most of his projects, he likes collecting minerals.\n* ''[[Dragon Ball]]''\n** [[Bulma]], a scientific genius, inventor and engineer.\n** [[List of Dragon Ball characters#Dr._Briefs|Dr. Briefs]], a brilliant scientist and founder of the Capsule Corporation. Bulma's father.\n* ''[[Mazinger Z]]''\n** [[List of Mazinger characters#Juzo Kabuto|Dr. Juzo Kabuto]], creator of Mazinger Z and father of its pilot, [[List of Mazinger characters#Koji Kabuto|Koji Kabuto]].\n** [[List of Mazinger characters#Dr. Yumi|Dr. Yumi]], Dr. Kabuto's colleague and father of Aphrodite A's pilot, [[List of Mazinger characters#Sayaka Yumi|Sayaka Yumi]].\n** [[List of Mazinger characters#Professors Sewashi, Nossori & Mori Mori|Professors Sewashi, Nossori & Mori Mori]], a trio of scientists who help Dr. Yumi.\n** [[List of Mazinger characters#Dr. Hell|Dr. Hell]], an evil scientist bent on world domination.\n* Hiroshi Ozora (''[[Moldiver]]''), a brilliant inventor for technological corporation ZIC and creator of the Mol-Unit.\n* ''[[My Hero Academia]]''\n** [[List of My Hero Academia characters#Other students|Mei Hatsume]], a brilliant but quirky student from the Support Course who invents her own hero gadgets.\n** [[List of My Hero Academia characters#Faculty and staff|Higari Maijima]], the chief of U.A.'s Costume Development Studio, responsible for creating, upgrading, and maintaining hero costumes.\n** [[List of My Hero Academia characters#Villains|Daruma Ujiko]], an evil genius working for All For One and the League of Villains.\n* [[List of Neon Genesis Evangelion characters#Ritsuko Akagi|Ritsuko Akagi]] (''[[Neon Genesis Evangelion]]''), NERV's head scientist \n* [[List of Sgt. Frog characters#Keroro Platoon|Kururu]] (''[[Sgt. Frog]]''), the resident genius of the Keroro Platoon, with a twisted and sadistic personality.\n* [[List of Tenchi Muyo! characters#Washu Hakubi|Washu Hakubi]] (''[[Tenchi Muyo!]]''),  the 20,000 years old self-proclaimed greatest scientific genius in the universe, mother of [[List of Tenchi Muyo! characters#Ryoko Hakubi|Ryoko]] and creator of the Soja and [[List of Tenchi Muyo! characters#Ryo-Ohki|Ryo-Ohki]].\n* [[List of Tiger & Bunny characters#Supporting characters|Saito]] (''[[Tiger & Bunny]]''), an engineer working for Apollon Media in charge of developing equipment for the company's superheroes.\n*Jotaro Kujo (''[[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]] Part 3: [[Stardust Crusaders]], Part 4: [[Diamond is Unbreakable]], Part 6: [[Stone Ocean]]''), a marine biologist. Jolyne's father.\n\n==In comics and graphic novels==\n=== DC Comics ===\n* [[Flash (Barry Allen)|Barry Allen]], a.k.a. [[Flash (comics)|The Flash]] (''[[The Flash (comic book)|The Flash]]'') \u2013 police scientist and superhero\n* [[Querl Dox]], a.k.a. [[Brainiac 5]] (''[[Legion of Super-Heroes]]'') \u2013  reputed to have a brain exponentially more powerful than a normal human\n* [[Flash (Jay Garrick)|Jay Garrick]], a.k.a. [[Flash (comics)|The Flash]] (''[[The Flash (comic book)|The Flash]]'') \u2013 research scientist, superhero and founding member of the [[Justice Society of America]]\n* [[Poison Ivy (comics)|Dr. Pamela Lillian Isley]], a.k.a. [[Poison Ivy (comics)|Poison Ivy]] (''[[Batman]]'') \u2013 supervillain scientist with an affinity towards poisonous plant.\n* [[Starman (Ted Knight)|Ted Knight]], a.k.a. Starman (''[[Starman (DC Comics Golden Age)|Starman]]'') \u2013 astronomer, expert scientist and superhero\n* [[Dr. Jon Osterman]], a.k.a. [[Dr. Manhattan]] (''[[Watchmen]]'') \u2013 nuclear physicist transformed by accident into a godlike super-being; while publicized as a superhero, he functions as the ultimate weapon for the United States military\n* [[Atom (Ray Palmer)|Ray Palmer]], a.k.a. [[Atom (comics)|Atom]] (''[[The Atom]]'') \u2013 professor of physics at Ivy University; able to shrink his body to varying degrees, even to sub-atomic level, and able to alter his mass to near infinite levels\n* [[Doctor Poison]] (''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'') \u2013 DC Comics supervillain, a mad scientist who specializes in chemistry and poisons\n* [[Alan Scott]] (''[[Green Lantern]]'') \u2013 engineer and the first Green Lantern\n* [[Doctor Sivana]], full name Thaddeus Bodog Sivana \u2013 world's wickedest scientist; arch-enemy of [[Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|Captain 